President Obama has declared a state of emergency in West Virginia due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Sandy. This declaration allows federal aid to supplement state and local response efforts. The Department of Homeland Security and FEMA will coordinate disaster relief efforts to help the local population and provide assistance for emergency measures to save lives, protect property, and ensure public health and safety. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and provide equipment as needed. Federal funding will cover 75% of emergency protective measures. Dolph A. Diemont has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.